2.2 Steps

2.2.1 Approved authoriser registration
Please note, a prerequisite of this process is that a senior staff member (“Open Publication Lead” - OPL) takes overall responsibility for administering the open oublication process including the authorisation of approvers and undertaking registration of open publication candidates.

Prospective “authorised approver” reads, agrees to and signs the Open Publication Responsibility Process (Chapter 4);
The open publication lead reviews the request and authorises appropriately.



2.2.2 Repository registration

An open publication registration pro forma (Chapter 5) is filled out and submitted to an appropriate oversight committee in the Trust;
The pro forma is reviewed and if no objections the repository is registered (with suitable records kept by the open publication lead).



2.2.3 Open publication approval

The repository is reviewed by an assigned authorised approver against the criteria set out in the open publication responsibility process;
If any criteria are not satisfied then issues are addressed between the authorised approver and the development team;
Once all criteria are passed, the repository is considered approved for open publication.



2.2.4 Open publication

A private repository is created in Github and the approved version of the repository is uploaded as a snapshot;
The relevant process for setting up regular repository checks is set up in Github;
The repository is published as a public repository.
